                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-135-off754 t18240407-135-crimeloc756"></join>. Between three and four o'clock in the afternoon I saw the prisoner going from master's door; I went up and asked him what he wanted, he said, he was very hungry. I looked under his coat, and saw one of master's boots, took it from him and asked if he had any thing else; he said, No, that his brother had the other boot, and if I would let him go he would call him back - I took him to the gate, and saw another person waiting for him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw a boy take up the boots and run away with them; he dropped one, I picked it up, and was taking it to the door when he came up.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 12.</p>
